# VM image build privileges

When building the example VM disk image, use **`/usr/bin/doas`** — not `sudo`.

- Run **`/home/kc/Work/alpine-make-vm-image/example/build.sh`** (absolute path), or `./example/build.sh` (it re-execs via doas).
- Host `doas.conf` permits only that script path; do not nest `doas alpine-make-vm-image` inside it.
- The script re-execs itself with `exec /usr/bin/doas "$BUILD_SH"` when not root, then runs `"$ROOT/alpine-make-vm-image"` directly.
- Image ownership after build uses `DOAS_USER` (and `SUDO_USER` as fallback).
